ost the whole of Ireland is said to have been converted to Christianity. He is also credited with codifying the laws of Ireland. In his Latin autobiography, as well as in later tradition, his name appears as <i>Patricius</i> ‘patrician’ (i.e. belonging to the Roman senatorial or noble class), but this may actually represent a Latinized form of some lost Celtic (British) name. In Ireland in particular, it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":37,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Patrick Cheswyk was born in 1345, in Northumberland, England, his father, Alexander Cheswyk, was 26 and his mother, Juliana Cheswyk, was 20. He had at least 2 daughters with Catherine. He died in 1391, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1345–1391":"1345–1391","1350–1381":"1350–1381","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","–1445":"–1445","1320–1370":"1320–1370","1325–1385":"1325–1385","1325":"1325","1445":"1445","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1320":"1320","9 April 1381":"9. aprill 1381","1385":"1385","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1381":"1381","1391":"1391","Cheswyk, Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1345–1391":"1345–1391","1350–1381":"1350–1381","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","–1445":"–1445","1320–1370":"1320–1370","1325–1385":"1325–1385","1325":"1325","1445"